{
  "doc_id": "40245",
  "text": "The analysis found two papers presenting the reviewers' reflective evaluation of the theme of debriefing topics. In these papers, it was reported that among studies with different topics including technical and nontechnical skills debriefing was effective [CITATION_1] LevettJones & Lapkin, 2014) . By contrast, [CITATION_2] highlighted a potential influence of different topics on debriefing. For example, they included a study reporting a greater preference for technical rather than cognitive focuses in debriefing content by participants [CITATION_3] . However, insufficient evidence of this aspect was observed in this present study for a conclusion to be reached. The limited evidence suggests that further investigation into what types of learning topics are valuable for debriefing is needed.",
